The '''Flying Bantha''' was an [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmospheric]] craft. The craft's design borrowed many design elements from the [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]], including stylized hull plates which mimicked an actual bantha's shape. The unknown devices located towards the rear of the vehicular unit shared many design elements with that of the [[Ubrikkian Industries/Legends|Ubrikkian]]-manufactured [[Bantha-II cargo skiff/Legends|Bantha-II cargo skiff]]; whether the Flying Bantha was made by the same company is unknown.

A vehicle of this type was utilized in an attempted theft of an unknown restaurant on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], around [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]]. The theft, however, would be unsuccessful. This event was coincidentally foreshadowed seconds earlier by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]], who had been discussing [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker's]] future with fellow Jedi Master [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]], as a sarcastic refusal towards training Anakin.

